    {
      "id": "sybil_14_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_14",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six powerplant with VarioCam Plus, delivering linear power delivery through a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. It has been meticulously sorted with an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent rear main seal replacement to ensure long-term mechanical integrity. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a Bilstein B12 Pro-Kit suspension upgrade that sharpens turn-in response and reduces body roll without compromising daily drivability. While the Arctic Silver metallic paint shows minor road-rash consistent with its mileage, the undercarriage is clean, and a recent borescope inspection confirmed no signs of cylinder bore scoring. Rolling on staggered 18-inch Carrera lightweight alloys wrapped in Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber, this 911 offers an authentic analog driving experience for the discerning enthusiast.",
